ic theories—had proven a spectacular failure. This richly detailed volume follows the history of such projects in three communist states—Poland, Hungary, and Czechoslovakia—and explores their varied, but largely disastrous, consequences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aEnvironmental degradationzEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnvironmental impact analysiszEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnvironmental policyzEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnvironmental policyzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aNaturexEffect of human beings onzEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial changezEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialismxEnvironmental aspectszEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh1 aBorvendég, Zsuzsanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJosephson, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlšáková, Doubravka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlšáková, Doubravka, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPalasik, Mária, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWysokińska, Beata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aŠtanzel, Arnošt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311099822140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781785332531?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781785332531423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781785332531/original  a978-3-11-099822-1  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKAL